notes: Includes Mephitis mephitis spissigrada (Puget Sound striped skunk)
Includes Mustela richardsonii anguinae, the only subspecies recognized in BC (endemic to Vancouver Island), as well as numerous other reported subspecies (requires review)

notes: Includes reports of numerous putative subspecies; currently the BC CDC does not even recognize Sorex monticola; "there has been disagreement over whether Sorex monticola is distinct from S. vagrans at the species level; most recent studies recognize S. monticola as a distinct species (e.g., Jones et al.1992; Hutterer in Wilson and Reeder 1993, 2005; Smith and Belk 1996).” (IUCN)
Tentatively includes Sorex vagrans vagrans and Sorex vagrans isolatus (Vancouver Island vagrant shrew), though some sources do not recognize the latter subspecies
